WEBVTT

00:41.208 --> 00:46.964
II'

00:54.596 --> 00:57.891
<i>Order, order!</i>

00:58.058 --> 01:02.938
In the matter of Lajos Kossuth
of Hungary.

01:03.105 --> 01:06.733
Who is this tormentor
of the Austrian monarchy?

01:06.900 --> 01:11.530
This exile now seeking asylum
in Britain?

01:11.697 --> 01:13.907
Mr. Speaker,
Kossuth is seen here

01:14.074 --> 01:16.868
as a hero of the common people,

01:17.035 --> 01:19.246
a cat set amongst
the fluttering pigeons

01:19.413 --> 01:21.999
of the royal families of Europe.

01:24.209 --> 01:26.545
Order.

01:26.712 --> 01:31.466
II'

01:39.558 --> 01:41.602
II'

01:44.021 --> 01:45.314
Herr Kossuth,

01:45.480 --> 01:47.274
I am the foreign secretary
of Great Britain,

01:47.441 --> 01:48.710
and you are most welcome,
friend.

01:48.734 --> 01:50.611
<i>Alas, these pigeons,</i>

01:50.777 --> 01:53.405
<i>they fear the conversation.</i>

01:53.572 --> 01:55.449
They are all a-commotion.

01:56.617 --> 01:57.617
Some of them

01:57.743 --> 01:59.411
have even fled their nests.

01:59.578 --> 02:03.707
II'

02:03.874 --> 02:06.126
We seem to be managing all right
without them.

02:12.633 --> 02:14.051
And... engage!

02:15.927 --> 02:18.096
Hi-yah!

02:19.931 --> 02:21.516
No mercy, princess.

02:27.230 --> 02:28.390
Know it's the Peninsular War,

02:28.523 --> 02:30.609
but... I'm unclear which battle.

02:30.776 --> 02:34.613
Fuentes de Onoro.

02:34.780 --> 02:36.740
Bertie is the duke
of Wellington.

02:36.907 --> 02:38.742
Naturally.

02:38.909 --> 02:40.345
As well as the
physical exercise, you see,

02:40.369 --> 02:42.079
there is also
a dramatic representation

02:42.245 --> 02:44.122
of military conquest.

02:44.289 --> 02:45.957
So his historical knowledge
is expanded.

02:46.124 --> 02:47.417
The English will never take us.

02:47.584 --> 02:49.127
<i>Vive Napoléon!</i>

02:50.462 --> 02:52.881
I wish there were a part for me.

02:53.048 --> 02:55.258
Do a party joust. BERTIE: Oh!

02:55.425 --> 02:56.425
Oh!

02:58.011 --> 02:59.304
Well played, sir.

03:05.852 --> 03:08.021
Your Majesty.

03:08.188 --> 03:10.023
Well fought, sir. Well played.

03:15.737 --> 03:18.865
Kossuth was received
"rapturously."

03:20.200 --> 03:21.910
Palmerston addressed him
as "friend."

03:22.077 --> 03:24.955
Palmerston is a blackguard,
and he must be disciplined.

03:25.122 --> 03:27.541
A simpler task were I not
100 miles from Parliament.

03:27.708 --> 03:30.108
We should demonstrate solidarity
with our royal counterparts,

03:30.252 --> 03:31.420
not offer sanctuary

03:31.586 --> 03:34.047
to those who seek
to annihilate us.

03:34.214 --> 03:35.632
Perhaps I shall write
to the emperor

03:35.799 --> 03:38.135
and explain the decision
to admit him was not yours.

03:38.301 --> 03:40.095
It wasn't.

03:40.262 --> 03:41.972
Because I wasn't there.

03:44.766 --> 03:46.184
Yes, of course, write a letter.

03:46.351 --> 03:47.951
How else can we participate
in government

03:48.103 --> 03:49.646
except by writing letters?

03:49.813 --> 03:51.106
- I didn't cheat.
- You did.

03:51.273 --> 03:52.816
Take that! Ow!

03:52.983 --> 03:55.360
Bertie! VICKY: That hurt.

03:55.527 --> 03:57.154
Be gracious in victory.

04:06.079 --> 04:09.207
God's bloody trousers.

04:09.374 --> 04:10.959
I did not enter royal service

04:11.126 --> 04:14.838
to go traipsing around
a garden clattering a drum.

04:15.005 --> 04:17.799
Give it up, then.

04:17.966 --> 04:19.217
Like this.

04:25.515 --> 04:27.768
I fear the queen
will be very wounded

04:27.934 --> 04:29.352
by Lord Palmerston's remarks.

04:29.519 --> 04:32.439
The man is a scoundrel.

04:32.606 --> 04:34.065
Incorrigible.

04:36.193 --> 04:39.029
I wonder how long
we shall remain here.

04:39.196 --> 04:42.574
Your Serene Highness must long
for the comforts of home.

04:42.741 --> 04:47.204
My only home, for now,
is with my sister;

04:47.370 --> 04:49.372
And if she chooses to live
on an island,

04:49.539 --> 04:51.208
so be it.

04:53.251 --> 04:57.380
Though I do wish my bedroom
had a view of the sea.

04:57.547 --> 04:58.566
My room looks onto the sea.

04:58.590 --> 04:59.590
Shall we exchange?

04:59.633 --> 05:00.967
How kind you are.

05:01.134 --> 05:02.344
But surely,

05:02.511 --> 05:05.388
you shall be returning home
soon?

05:05.555 --> 05:08.558
Your husband must be pining
for you.

05:08.725 --> 05:12.145
Do you know
what that man has done?

05:12.312 --> 05:15.524
He's sent our son away
to boarding school.

05:15.690 --> 05:16.817
The child is six.

05:19.319 --> 05:23.782
It is better that I am here.

05:23.949 --> 05:26.535
Bertie answers to nothing,
nothing!

05:26.701 --> 05:28.036
How am I supposed to teach a boy

05:28.203 --> 05:29.329
that...

05:29.496 --> 05:31.832
Oh, but your concern is
the report

05:31.998 --> 05:33.750
of your spy in London»
he speaks of what?

05:33.917 --> 05:35.517
Uh, crowds cheering Palmerston,
no doubt.

05:35.585 --> 05:36.962
Albert, this is not from London.

05:37.128 --> 05:38.964
It's from Francatelli.

05:39.130 --> 05:40.841
The cook.

05:41.007 --> 05:42.050
He's resigned.

05:42.217 --> 05:43.260
Then he shall be replaced.

05:43.426 --> 05:44.511
Victoria, really,

05:44.678 --> 05:46.318
this is such
a, a trivial domestic matter.

05:46.471 --> 05:48.807
Drina, if you will permit,

05:48.974 --> 05:50.308
when we return to London...

05:50.475 --> 05:52.155
Did you know anything
about this, Skerrett?

05:53.311 --> 05:54.813
No, ma'am.

05:57.274 --> 05:58.942
Please, um...

05:59.109 --> 06:00.402
Would you mind?

06:05.699 --> 06:07.284
Unleashing your
vitriol on Skerrett

06:07.450 --> 06:08.719
is not going to make
the situation better.

06:08.743 --> 06:10.161
Vitriol?

06:13.874 --> 06:16.877
II'

06:18.670 --> 06:20.297
I didn't believe
you really would.

06:20.463 --> 06:22.841
Well, Mrs. Francatelli,

06:23.008 --> 06:24.593
ldid.

06:24.759 --> 06:26.595
And did the world end?

06:26.761 --> 06:28.346
More or less.

06:28.513 --> 06:30.473
They've been at
each other's throats for weeks.

06:32.601 --> 06:33.828
Problem is,
she's queen of England,

06:33.852 --> 06:36.479
but he's king
of the Isle of Wight.

06:40.275 --> 06:42.986
Your turn, my honey.

06:44.654 --> 06:48.283
Do it.

06:48.450 --> 06:49.951
You don't have to say it
to her face.

06:50.118 --> 06:50.952
You can write it, like I did.

06:51.119 --> 06:52.245
No.

06:53.997 --> 06:57.500
No, I... I have to say it.

07:00.045 --> 07:01.397
The natural ebb and flow
of the staff, Victoria,

07:01.421 --> 07:02.773
is something you must not
allow yourself

07:02.797 --> 07:03.858
to be distracted by... Must?

07:03.882 --> 07:04.942
Must? ...While we are here.

07:04.966 --> 07:06.593
It is not what matters.

07:06.760 --> 07:08.845
Here, what matters is
the children.

07:09.012 --> 07:11.181
Here, they can be occupied.

07:11.348 --> 07:13.266
It is what corrupts
the aristocracy,

07:13.433 --> 07:15.268
to have no occupation.

07:15.435 --> 07:17.187
Bertie, for example;

07:17.354 --> 07:18.873
I want Bertie to be able
to make things,

07:18.897 --> 07:20.374
to, to repair them
when they are broken,

07:20.398 --> 07:21.566
to, to grow the wheat,

07:21.733 --> 07:23.902
make the flour, bake the bread.

07:24.069 --> 07:27.781
But most of all,
I want him to... read.

07:29.199 --> 07:30.784
He does not read.

07:30.951 --> 07:34.162
If our children are going
to be of value,

07:34.329 --> 07:35.914
it is their duty to be the best.

07:36.081 --> 07:38.333
<i>Our duty to make them so.</i>

07:38.500 --> 07:41.086
I designed this house
to be a place

07:41.252 --> 07:43.004
where our children
can become superb.

07:43.171 --> 07:45.590
Palmerston has invited Kossuth

07:45.757 --> 07:47.676
to dine with him
in his London club.

07:47.842 --> 07:49.820
Albert, that is an
insubordination I cannot ignore.

07:49.844 --> 07:52.681
He's lied through his teeth
about the Chartists.

07:52.847 --> 07:54.474
And then he... swaggers about,

07:54.641 --> 07:56.309
openly calling me a coward.

07:56.476 --> 07:57.852
Albert, I must return

07:58.019 --> 07:59.396
to London. No.

08:01.606 --> 08:03.358
No, Victoria.

08:05.110 --> 08:06.820
Well, then, London must come
to me.

08:08.571 --> 08:13.660
II'

08:24.504 --> 08:26.339
Without your train, Henry,

08:26.506 --> 08:28.341
if that's possible.

08:31.136 --> 08:32.554
Gentlemen,

08:32.721 --> 08:36.307
the prime minister and I
have some private business.

08:36.474 --> 08:38.977
Thank you.

08:47.360 --> 08:48.903
We haven't time.

08:49.070 --> 08:50.155
It is not a suggestion.

08:50.321 --> 08:52.699
It's a royal command.

08:52.866 --> 08:54.451
Oh, well.

08:54.617 --> 08:57.120
We couldn't possible refuse
one of those, could we?

09:00.498 --> 09:04.294
II'

09:11.092 --> 09:14.888
Can we explore the cave, Papa?

09:15.055 --> 09:16.389
Lead on.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.641
Papa, look!

09:21.895 --> 09:23.730
Well, we must make the most

09:23.897 --> 09:26.733
of what the prince calls,
"the amenities."

09:26.900 --> 09:29.444
However unamenable
they might seem.

09:32.363 --> 09:34.741
You'll be all
right, Your Majesty.

09:34.908 --> 09:36.534
Do you suppose
it's possible, actually,

09:36.701 --> 09:39.537
to breathe under the water?

09:39.704 --> 09:42.415
I really don't know, ma'am.

09:42.582 --> 09:43.666
Fish do it.

09:43.833 --> 09:45.251
Hmm.

09:49.589 --> 09:52.425
Right.

09:57.639 --> 10:00.308
II'

10:25.875 --> 10:28.128
Your Majesty!

10:29.796 --> 10:30.964
Your Majesty.

10:39.222 --> 10:40.223
Drina.

10:46.229 --> 10:47.564
Well, lthink we have established

10:47.730 --> 10:48.940
the queen of England is...

10:49.107 --> 10:51.234
not a fish.

10:58.867 --> 11:02.996
We came at once, as
the situation is clearly urgent.

11:03.163 --> 11:06.708
How may we be of assistance
to Your Majesty?

11:17.427 --> 11:18.845
This room is very...

11:21.222 --> 11:22.432
<i>N001'!-</i>

11:22.599 --> 11:24.142
I designed it myself.

11:24.309 --> 11:25.852
Yes, I can see that.

11:26.019 --> 11:27.770
Lord John,

11:27.937 --> 11:29.689
concerning this Kossuth.

11:29.856 --> 11:30.982
It is paramount

11:31.149 --> 11:33.318
we do not antagonize
the Austrian monarchy.

11:33.484 --> 11:35.069
I am addressing
my prime minister.

11:35.236 --> 11:36.654
Kossuth's reception into Britain

11:36.821 --> 11:39.616
makes my country look
duplicitous and weak.

11:39.782 --> 11:41.159
With respect, ma'am...

11:41.326 --> 11:42.970
There is no respect
in what you have to say,

11:42.994 --> 11:44.078
Lord Palmerston.

11:44.245 --> 11:45.965
Saying "with respect"
does not put it there.

11:46.122 --> 11:49.167
These are matters
of foreign diplomacy, ma'am.

11:49.334 --> 11:50.752
I am your foreign secretary.

11:50.919 --> 11:52.420
And we shall come to that.

11:54.589 --> 11:57.133
Understand a member of
your cabinet has invited Kossuth

11:57.300 --> 11:58.760
to dine with him...
Is that correct?

11:58.927 --> 12:00.929
May... May I speak?

12:01.095 --> 12:02.222
If there is time

12:02.388 --> 12:03.973
in your busy schedule of dinners

12:04.140 --> 12:05.558
with regicidal anarchists.

12:05.725 --> 12:07.810
Lajos Kossuth is not a regicide,

12:07.977 --> 12:09.312
and he's not an anarchist.

12:09.479 --> 12:11.731
He's beheld his people
being taxed to death

12:11.898 --> 12:13.024
by a rapacious tyrant.

12:13.191 --> 12:14.609
As my minister of state,

12:14.776 --> 12:16.256
you will undertake to do
three things.

12:16.361 --> 12:17.713
One: You will retract
your invitation

12:17.737 --> 12:19.572
to dine with Kossuth.

12:19.739 --> 12:21.407
Two: You will see him cleanly

12:21.574 --> 12:22.992
off the premises of my country.

12:23.159 --> 12:25.012
Three: You will write to
the crowned heads of Europe,

12:25.036 --> 12:27.997
assuring them
of my government's allegiance.

12:28.164 --> 12:30.583
Is there anything on that list
you do not understand?

12:32.126 --> 12:35.004
Your Majesty is
pellucidly clear.

12:35.171 --> 12:38.299
Then why do you grin at me?

12:38.466 --> 12:41.803
I cannot help the disposition
of my face, ma'am.

12:43.638 --> 12:45.390
Or is that thing number four'?

12:49.936 --> 12:53.147
Please forgive
me for being so bold,

12:53.314 --> 12:54.565
but am I right

12:54.732 --> 12:58.278
in assuming you share
my opinion of Palmerston?

12:58.444 --> 13:01.030
That the man is
a preening buffoon?

13:01.197 --> 13:05.285
Palmerston is
morbidly incapable of not preening,

13:05.451 --> 13:06.577
but he is no buffoon.

13:06.744 --> 13:08.997
I'd sooner he were lolling

13:09.163 --> 13:11.666
in my cabinet,
causing irritation

13:11.833 --> 13:13.334
than ranked
on the opposite bench,

13:13.501 --> 13:15.336
whipping up the mob against me.

13:15.503 --> 13:17.046
Hmm.

13:17.213 --> 13:19.882
I trust you shall stay
for a day or two?

13:20.049 --> 13:22.719
Isensed
the queen wished us gone.

13:22.885 --> 13:25.680
Oh, well, you have traveled
such a long way.

13:25.847 --> 13:28.433
It would be discourteous
not to invite you.

13:28.599 --> 13:30.310
Ah.

13:30.476 --> 13:31.602
Here.

13:34.147 --> 13:38.318
It's best to eat just the top.

13:40.445 --> 13:42.488
Oh, Russell, good heavens.

13:42.655 --> 13:45.867
You must cook them first.

13:47.327 --> 13:49.078
Ah, good day.

13:49.245 --> 13:50.538
Papa.

13:50.705 --> 13:51.998
My, my-

13:52.165 --> 13:54.500
<i>Good.</i>

13:54.667 --> 13:58.671
Russell, it is, um,
safe to eat this.

14:10.725 --> 14:12.101
Bertie.

14:14.062 --> 14:15.188
Bertie!

14:24.113 --> 14:25.281
I'd, um...

14:25.448 --> 14:27.700
I'd like to exchange rooms
with Princess Feodora.

14:27.867 --> 14:30.078
She wishes
for a view of the sea.

14:30.244 --> 14:31.412
Will you arrange it?

14:31.579 --> 14:33.498
Of course, Your Grace.

14:33.664 --> 14:36.125
Though, uh...

14:36.292 --> 14:38.878
The sea's a fine thing
to look upon.

14:41.255 --> 14:42.524
It makes no difference
what I look upon

14:42.548 --> 14:44.467
if it isn't my little boy.

14:46.135 --> 14:48.679
I'm so sorry you have to be
parted from him.

14:48.846 --> 14:50.807
It must, uh...

14:50.973 --> 14:52.058
Forgive me, I...

14:57.146 --> 14:59.583
Prime minister and the foreign
secretary are here, Your Grace.

14:59.607 --> 15:02.318
Lord Palmerston has come?

15:04.862 --> 15:07.031
Joseph, isn't it?

15:18.876 --> 15:22.046
II'

15:25.550 --> 15:28.553
Naught, multiplied by two.

15:28.719 --> 15:29.804
Two.

15:29.971 --> 15:33.641
No, naught has no value.

15:33.808 --> 15:36.894
Try to imagine the, the two
and the naught on the page.

15:37.061 --> 15:38.146
20.

15:38.312 --> 15:40.064
Albert.

15:40.231 --> 15:41.983
Can it be true
you've invited...?

15:42.150 --> 15:47.113
This boy's refusal to learn
is preposterous.

15:47.280 --> 15:49.157
He can hear you, you know.

15:51.868 --> 15:54.120
All right.

15:54.287 --> 15:57.457
Let's leave arithmetic behind,

15:57.623 --> 16:01.294
turn our attention to French.

16:01.461 --> 16:02.753
I shall set a test.

16:02.920 --> 16:05.089
Thank you.

16:05.256 --> 16:06.632
This way.

16:37.580 --> 16:38.664
Forgive me, Your Grace,

16:38.831 --> 16:41.626
there is something come adrift.

16:44.003 --> 16:45.129
Uh...

17:09.862 --> 17:12.031
Where's your husband, Duchess?

17:15.576 --> 17:17.495
The man to whom you are married?

17:18.913 --> 17:20.164
He's in London.

17:20.331 --> 17:22.291
Excellent.

17:24.961 --> 17:27.713
It is shocking
that you find it excellent

17:27.880 --> 17:29.048
that my husband isn't here.

17:29.215 --> 17:30.299
Shocking.

17:31.717 --> 17:34.470
Excessively shocking.

17:34.637 --> 17:37.598
But also excellent.

17:44.689 --> 17:49.569
II'

17:57.952 --> 17:59.412
Henry.

17:59.579 --> 18:01.497
How is Lady Palmerston?

18:01.664 --> 18:03.207
As ever.

18:03.374 --> 18:05.876
In charge, full of plans.

18:06.043 --> 18:08.129
It's kind of you to ask.

18:22.143 --> 18:24.312
Lord Palmerston. Ma'am.

18:24.478 --> 18:25.980
Will you make up our table?

18:26.147 --> 18:27.273
Ma'am.

18:32.570 --> 18:35.031
Now that I have you
within range, sir,

18:35.197 --> 18:37.074
I want to know:
Why did you suppose

18:37.241 --> 18:39.160
that I would not be offended

18:39.327 --> 18:44.498
to hear myself dismissed...
as a pigeon?

18:44.665 --> 18:47.293
I did not suppose it, ma'am.

18:47.460 --> 18:49.086
In truth, I...

18:49.253 --> 18:50.796
didn't expect you to hear
my analogy

18:50.963 --> 18:52.548
from... such a distance.

18:52.715 --> 18:53.942
Whenever statesmen plead
"in truth,"

18:53.966 --> 18:56.969
I cannot help
but doubt their word.

18:57.136 --> 18:59.513
I can assure you
I wasn't pleading.

18:59.680 --> 19:01.766
I merely sought to engage
the attention of the House.

19:01.932 --> 19:03.601
You were playing to the gallery.

19:03.768 --> 19:06.228
Something we all relish, ma'am.

19:09.482 --> 19:12.860
I read in the newspaper, ma'am.

19:13.027 --> 19:14.904
The German states
are now considered

19:15.071 --> 19:16.364
as safe.

19:16.530 --> 19:17.730
Thought it might be something;

19:17.865 --> 19:19.092
That would be
of particular interest

19:19.116 --> 19:20.910
to... Her Serene Highness.

19:21.077 --> 19:23.329
Oh, that's wonderful news.

19:23.496 --> 19:24.580
Albert. ALBERT: Hmm?

19:24.747 --> 19:26.624
We must make arrangements
accordingly.

19:26.791 --> 19:28.834
Drina,

19:29.001 --> 19:31.212
might 1 have your permission
to {withdraw?

19:33.506 --> 19:34.799
I don't understand.

19:34.965 --> 19:37.802
Surely you long to be reunited
with your family?

19:37.968 --> 19:39.553
In Langenburg,
there is still such...

19:39.720 --> 19:41.389
hatred.

19:41.555 --> 19:42.890
And I am, of course,

19:43.057 --> 19:45.309
a blood relative of a queen.

19:47.228 --> 19:49.146
Were I to return, my life,

19:49.313 --> 19:53.484
the lives of my children,

19:53.651 --> 19:55.027
they would be in...

19:55.194 --> 19:57.196
great danger.

19:57.363 --> 20:00.616
My own husband tells me so.

20:00.783 --> 20:03.035
Is this your understanding?

20:03.202 --> 20:05.621
I cannot say, ma'am.

20:05.788 --> 20:07.140
But I do have informants
in the city

20:07.164 --> 20:09.542
and I will interrogate them
closely.

20:09.709 --> 20:12.336
Anything to assist a princess.

20:12.503 --> 20:15.840
And until then,

20:16.006 --> 20:18.426
there is absolutely no question
of you going anywhere.

20:18.592 --> 20:21.554
You shall remain here,

20:21.721 --> 20:23.264
with us.

20:27.101 --> 20:33.774
II'

20:37.278 --> 20:40.281
This <i>carpet</i> is <i>very mouvementé.</i>

20:40.448 --> 20:45.745
Do you suppose the prince
designed it, as well?

20:45.911 --> 20:49.749
It was considerate of you
to offer to assist me.

20:49.915 --> 20:51.208
Thank you.

20:51.375 --> 20:54.462
"Considerate" is one word.

20:57.798 --> 21:01.886
My informers in Langenburg
reported back to me

21:02.052 --> 21:03.804
just the other day.

21:03.971 --> 21:06.557
They said, quite categorically,
that it's perfectly safe

21:06.724 --> 21:08.726
for you to return home
when you wish,

21:08.893 --> 21:10.895
as you well know.

21:11.061 --> 21:14.482
But I am the sister of...
Your Serene Highness,

21:14.648 --> 21:17.318
the dissenters have
no interest in you.

21:17.485 --> 21:21.322
You simply want to stay
in England.

21:21.489 --> 21:25.367
What sort of trick
do you play on me?

21:25.534 --> 21:28.120
What sort of trick
do you play on her?

21:43.511 --> 21:45.304
<i>I</i> know you do not care

21:45.471 --> 21:46.680
for my house.

21:46.847 --> 21:48.849
I love your house.

21:49.016 --> 21:50.810
I love you,

21:50.976 --> 21:53.771
and the children
you have blessed me with, but...

21:53.938 --> 21:56.106
The troubles of my
country do not simply vanish

21:56.273 --> 21:58.734
because I can no longer see them
from my window.

22:00.152 --> 22:01.362
What?

22:01.529 --> 22:02.696
I did not speak.

22:02.863 --> 22:05.282
Yet, as you intended, I heard.

22:05.449 --> 22:07.827
You radiate sullen disapproval.

22:07.993 --> 22:11.372
No, it's not disapproval,
Victoria.

22:11.539 --> 22:13.332
I'm afraid.

22:13.499 --> 22:15.101
You demonstrated your authority
to Palmerston,

22:15.125 --> 22:17.211
you told him what you wanted,
he acquiesced.

22:17.378 --> 22:19.481
Whether or not he will actually
carry out what you want

22:19.505 --> 22:21.674
when he returns to London...
That man's trouble is,

22:21.841 --> 22:23.092
he's in love,

22:23.259 --> 22:26.303
with the people being
in love with him.

22:26.470 --> 22:28.931
This is my fear:

22:29.098 --> 22:30.808
That it may also be true of you.

22:32.810 --> 22:35.563
That your heart craves

22:35.729 --> 22:37.815
adulation.

22:39.942 --> 22:41.360
"Craves adulation"?

22:41.527 --> 22:43.529
That's why you find it
so hard to be here.

22:43.696 --> 22:46.448
Deprived of it.

22:52.746 --> 22:55.457
It is your prerogative

22:55.624 --> 23:00.421
to favor me
with your analysis, Albert.

23:00.588 --> 23:02.172
Mine to disregard it.

23:04.592 --> 23:06.093
Now I wish to sleep.

23:12.016 --> 23:13.142
Good night.

23:43.839 --> 23:46.717
