27:11.839 --> 27:13.674
Do make sure I don't.

27:13.841 --> 27:17.094
That would be the wise thing.

27:17.261 --> 27:20.931
The queen and her husband
detest you.

27:21.098 --> 27:24.393
How that antipathy would swell

27:24.560 --> 27:27.229
if they learned
about last night.

27:27.396 --> 27:30.232
II'

27:30.399 --> 27:32.109
Don't sulk.

27:32.276 --> 27:33.735
It doesn't suit you.

27:33.902 --> 27:37.322
II'

27:37.489 --> 27:39.032
Are we allowed
to discuss our son

27:39.199 --> 27:41.743
without you losing your temper?

27:41.910 --> 27:43.537
Bertie has
the perfect situation here

27:43.704 --> 27:44.913
in which to learn.

27:45.080 --> 27:46.307
Yau use that as a pretext
to? Keep us here.

27:46.331 --> 27:47.749
I see.

27:47.916 --> 27:50.544
And do you use Kossuth
as a pretext for us to leave?

27:51.879 --> 27:53.148
What I endeavor to achieve
with Bertie

27:53.172 --> 27:55.090
is an investment in the future.

27:55.257 --> 27:57.551
We, we cannot mindlessly exist
in the present.

27:57.718 --> 28:00.012
But is it mindless to consider
the respect of my subjects

28:00.179 --> 28:01.889
a thing worth having?

28:02.055 --> 28:03.775
Does it actually matter
whether the poor boy

28:03.932 --> 28:05.809
can or cannot
conjugate his verbs

28:05.976 --> 28:07.769
if he might not have
a throne to inherit?

28:07.936 --> 28:09.855
How dare you construe
that as vanity.

28:10.022 --> 28:13.108
The throne, Victoria, is secure.

28:13.275 --> 28:15.319
Yes, but currently unoccupied.

28:27.623 --> 28:30.876
I sought your dismissal,
you know.

28:33.337 --> 28:34.504
Lord John advised against it.

28:35.923 --> 28:37.090
Hm.

28:39.343 --> 28:40.761
Now make your case
about Kossuth.

28:42.971 --> 28:46.183
It is desirable...

28:46.350 --> 28:47.559
for the world to see

28:47.726 --> 28:49.046
that Britain is not afraid
of him.

28:49.186 --> 28:50.938
So, let him have his say.

28:51.104 --> 28:54.691
And when he has
delighted us enough,

28:54.858 --> 28:56.902
let us send him on
to somebody else.

28:59.905 --> 29:03.283
The <i>sands</i> will close over
the imprint of his visit,

29:03.450 --> 29:07.746
whereas Ycur Majesty
will be rightly celebrated

29:07.913 --> 29:09.831
for her tolerance
and willingness

29:09.998 --> 29:13.710
to let her subjects
have their free debate.

29:16.171 --> 29:18.757
You are the only constitutional
monarch in Europe.

29:18.924 --> 29:23.679
And your understanding of that
is clear for all to see.

29:23.845 --> 29:27.391
It's no bad thing
to keep the people on your side.

29:29.726 --> 29:33.397
Perplexing to hear you
style yourself my admirer.

29:33.563 --> 29:35.691
Not yours, ma'am.

29:35.857 --> 29:37.442
Britain's.

29:37.609 --> 29:41.822
Perhaps, after all,
you and I do think alike.

29:43.991 --> 29:45.242
Just a little.

29:45.409 --> 29:48.495
II'

29:49.663 --> 29:52.874
In any one day,

29:53.041 --> 29:54.126
you are allowed

29:54.293 --> 29:58.046
precisely 20 minutes of liberty.

29:58.213 --> 30:00.566
I think we just made pretty good use of it.
The rest of the time,

30:00.590 --> 30:02.759
she rings that bell,
day Qr night...

30:02.926 --> 30:04.195
Mothering Sunday
I get the whole day off.

30:04.219 --> 30:05.637
V0U go running.

30:05.804 --> 30:08.849
If that bell had rung just now,

30:09.016 --> 30:12.436
you'd have upped and gone,
even then, wouldn't you?

30:20.610 --> 30:22.738
My love...

30:22.904 --> 30:24.990
Now is the perfect moment.

30:25.157 --> 30:25.991
She's got a new child,
she's got...

30:26.158 --> 30:28.618
But she knew what I was.

30:28.785 --> 30:30.245
What I'd done.

30:30.412 --> 30:32.789
And she waved it all away.

30:32.956 --> 30:35.375
She gave me a new life.

30:41.631 --> 30:44.217
It's me offering you
a new life now.

30:44.384 --> 30:50.557
II'

30:59.483 --> 31:02.277
Sophie Monmouth
is out of bounds.

31:02.444 --> 31:05.572
Not to be used
for the amorous complications

31:05.739 --> 31:07.282
you have in mind.

31:10.035 --> 31:13.663
I ask this in remembrance
of our own complications.

31:15.123 --> 31:16.708
She cries out for something
we both know

31:16.875 --> 31:18.919
you will never give her.

31:19.086 --> 31:22.089
It would be cruel, Henry.

31:22.255 --> 31:29.054
II'

31:29.221 --> 31:31.306
I withdraw my artillery.

31:35.560 --> 31:39.815
II'

31:43.985 --> 31:48.865
II'

31:52.285 --> 31:55.038
It's truly the most
outstandingly vulgar building

31:55.205 --> 31:56.498
I've ever seen in my life.

31:58.166 --> 31:59.501
It is incongruous.

32:00.669 --> 32:02.796
A want of congruity

32:02.963 --> 32:04.047
is the least of its sins.

32:06.383 --> 32:09.177
And what of your sins, my lord?

32:13.306 --> 32:16.643
What an alarming question.

32:16.810 --> 32:19.210
Alas, I cannot stay to ventilate
the matter with you further.

32:19.271 --> 32:20.355
I have affairs of state.

32:20.522 --> 32:21.606
Shall I see you later?

32:21.773 --> 32:23.024
For what purpose, Duchess?

32:23.191 --> 32:24.484
For the purpose

32:24.651 --> 32:28.071
of consolidating
our acquaintance.

32:28.238 --> 32:30.824
Our acquaintance
is sufficiently consolidated.

32:30.991 --> 32:32.701
Don't you think?

32:34.035 --> 32:35.454
Listen.

32:35.620 --> 32:40.208
All can offer you
is pleasure and (distraction,

32:40.375 --> 32:41.769
and you may think
that's what you need,

32:41.793 --> 32:45.172
but it isn't.

32:45.338 --> 32:51.094
What you need,
I am not at liberty to give you.

32:51.261 --> 32:53.346
I'm so sorry.

33:01.855 --> 33:07.736
II'

33:10.322 --> 33:11.448
Get out of the way!

33:36.598 --> 33:37.849
Silly tears.

33:41.019 --> 33:42.246
Why must I look to seek comfort

33:42.270 --> 33:44.231
where it cannot possibly
be found?

33:46.775 --> 33:48.401
Oh, please say something.

33:49.861 --> 33:51.112
Your Grace, I...

33:53.573 --> 33:54.824
Listen.

33:56.535 --> 34:00.205
Can you hear the waves
folding over on the beach?

34:06.169 --> 34:10.215
It frightens me a little...
The sea.

34:10.382 --> 34:12.759
It makes me feel alive.

34:25.230 --> 34:26.648
Victoria.

34:26.815 --> 34:28.709
The new Austrian emperor
has dispatched ambassadors

34:28.733 --> 34:31.570
to every European country
except ours.

34:31.736 --> 34:34.239
Mine. Well,
clearly he finds us a liability...

34:34.406 --> 34:35.574
Leopold told me as much.

34:35.740 --> 34:39.869
Kossuth must be evicted.

34:40.036 --> 34:41.746
I have changed my mind.

34:45.542 --> 34:48.712
I have agreed that he should
be honored with a dinner.

34:50.046 --> 34:52.507
At which Palmerston
should preside.

34:52.674 --> 34:54.676
Two of a kind.

34:57.220 --> 34:59.340
He's told you that your people
will love you for this,

34:59.472 --> 35:02.517
and you wrap his words
around you like

35:03.977 --> 35:05.103
cloak.

35:12.652 --> 35:13.737
Skerrett...

35:13.903 --> 35:16.406
Oh, I do apologize,
Your Majesty.

35:19.743 --> 35:21.661
Are you quite well?

35:23.538 --> 35:25.415
What's the matter? Tell me.

35:27.751 --> 35:30.003
Have you broken something?

35:30.170 --> 35:31.963
Come on,
you know I shan“: Be angry.

35:32.130 --> 35:34.507
I desire to leave your service,
ma'am.

35:37.260 --> 35:39.179
For the sake of my marriage.

35:41.723 --> 35:43.141
Marriage.

35:43.308 --> 35:46.770
To Mr. Francatelli.

35:46.936 --> 35:50.023
I had no wish to keep it secret
from you, ma'am, I just...

35:53.151 --> 35:55.278
I just couldn't...

35:57.364 --> 36:00.367
It is time...

36:00.533 --> 36:01.618
for me to go.

36:01.785 --> 36:09.376
II'

36:09.542 --> 36:11.252
I'm so sorry.

36:11.419 --> 36:16.299
II'

36:29.646 --> 36:36.611
II'

37:01.886 --> 37:02.971
Hm.

37:06.057 --> 37:09.602
In what respect does une vache
translate as "a hammer"?

37:09.769 --> 37:13.356
How would one milk a hammer?

37:13.523 --> 37:15.650
I don't bloody know!

37:18.903 --> 37:21.239
Right.

37:21.406 --> 37:23.283
Go to your room... shall follow.

37:23.450 --> 37:25.285
Please don't.
Please do not interfere.

37:25.452 --> 37:27.120
Please don't bully my child.

37:27.287 --> 37:30.832
Victoria, I have never bullied
our child, and I never shall,

37:30.999 --> 37:33.018
but it must be made clear to the boy.
It's perfectly clear

37:33.042 --> 37:35.003
how little you value
his attempts to please you.

37:35.170 --> 37:36.171
Clear to us all.

37:36.337 --> 37:37.815
Victoria, by God,
you're being inappropriate.

37:37.839 --> 37:39.424
If you find me
inappropriate, Albert,

37:39.591 --> 37:40.818
either remark upon it privately,

37:40.842 --> 37:41.885
or if you insist

37:42.051 --> 37:43.571
on drawing the matter
to the attention of the court,

37:43.595 --> 37:45.638
address me with respect.

37:45.805 --> 37:50.018
If you were deserving
of respect, Your Majesty...

37:53.188 --> 37:54.355
then I should.

37:58.902 --> 38:01.613
II'

38:12.123 --> 38:15.293
II'

38:20.006 --> 38:21.758
Really.

38:21.925 --> 38:24.928
One quite understands.

38:26.179 --> 38:28.890
The wine was not good.

38:31.518 --> 38:33.394
May I speak frankly?

38:35.897 --> 38:39.067
I agree with you.

38:39.234 --> 38:44.072
Oh, how I wish we could return
to London so we could breathe.

38:45.657 --> 38:47.200
My dear, the Peninsular War,

38:47.367 --> 38:49.452
surely it never
went on this long.

38:53.081 --> 38:57.126
Albert is a kind man,

38:57.293 --> 39:00.505
but it is observed

39:00.672 --> 39:02.465
that he constricts you.

39:06.427 --> 39:07.554
Observed by whom?

39:07.720 --> 39:09.389
Who says such a thing?

39:09.556 --> 39:11.182
People of little consequence.

39:11.349 --> 39:13.351
Silly, talkative women.

39:16.563 --> 39:19.107
My only desire
is to serve you, Drina,

39:19.274 --> 39:23.820
but if I hear something
detrimental to your authority,

39:23.987 --> 39:25.363
I must tell it.

39:25.530 --> 39:29.367
That is all I say.

39:29.534 --> 39:31.452
Now cut off my head.

39:33.663 --> 39:35.874
I know you find me disagreeable.

39:36.040 --> 39:37.500
Fee...

39:39.836 --> 39:42.255
How could you say such a thing?

39:42.422 --> 39:46.301
II'

39:53.975 --> 39:56.603
Of course.

39:56.769 --> 39:59.480
She is upset.

39:59.647 --> 40:02.358
To be obliged to withdraw
from London

40:02.525 --> 40:03.776
is insupportable.

40:03.943 --> 40:05.528
I see that.

40:05.695 --> 40:09.157
May I... speak frankly?

40:11.826 --> 40:15.246
It seems to me
that there is a simple test

40:15.413 --> 40:19.792
whether or not a man
has married the right woman.

40:19.959 --> 40:23.296
The man must ask himself:
This wife of mine,

40:23.463 --> 40:26.507
does she increase me
or diminish me?

40:26.674 --> 40:28.384
Am I more of a man
because of her?

40:28.551 --> 40:30.094
Or less?

40:30.261 --> 40:34.849
Marriage to Victoria
has undoubtedly increased me.

40:35.016 --> 40:37.685
It continues to increase me.

40:37.852 --> 40:40.647
I am infinitely more a man
because of her.

40:42.065 --> 40:43.983
<i>Good.</i>

40:44.150 --> 40:46.027
Then all is well.

40:46.194 --> 40:47.946
This will blow over.

40:49.614 --> 40:53.409
My sister is a little
<i>difficile</i> at present.

40:53.576 --> 40:54.994
That is the strain

40:55.161 --> 40:58.873
of the feminine humors.

40:59.040 --> 41:01.542
Repeated childbirth.

41:01.709 --> 41:03.252
Makes women stupid.

41:03.419 --> 41:07.006
Are you suggesting
that Victoria's sanity depends

41:07.173 --> 41:08.841
on she and I having no more...

41:10.843 --> 41:12.512
"children?"

41:12.679 --> 41:13.805
No! No.

41:13.972 --> 41:15.932
Of course not!

41:16.099 --> 41:18.601
The disorder of her mind
is strictly temporary.

41:22.105 --> 41:23.940
Not at all like
her dear grandpapds.

41:39.998 --> 41:41.238
Will that be all, Your Majesty?

41:41.290 --> 41:42.667
Apparently so.

41:42.834 --> 41:47.463
II'

41:59.475 --> 42:06.399
II'

42:27.045 --> 42:28.880
What day is it today?

42:29.047 --> 42:30.423
Remind me.

42:32.425 --> 42:33.259
Sunday, Mr. Penge.

42:33.426 --> 42:34.802
Sunday.

42:34.969 --> 42:40.850
And what do we do
on a Sunday morning,

42:41.017 --> 42:42.268
wherever we happen to be?

42:45.021 --> 42:47.815
We go to church,
you bloody heathen!

42:47.982 --> 42:49.317
Yes, Mr. Penge.

42:49.484 --> 42:50.818
"Yes, Mr. Penge."

42:50.985 --> 42:53.071
You're not in Chatsworth, now.
Sir...

42:53.237 --> 42:55.364
And don't speak
while I'm shouting at you!

42:58.034 --> 42:59.368
Where were you?

43:01.537 --> 43:03.331
Bathing, Mr. Penge.

43:03.498 --> 43:05.249
Bathing.

43:05.416 --> 43:07.210
In the sea.

43:13.966 --> 43:15.259
Do you smell that?

43:17.345 --> 43:18.971
That's your goose.

43:19.138 --> 43:21.641
Well and truly cooked.

43:32.443 --> 43:36.030
To whom do you write
so assiduously, Duchess?

43:36.197 --> 43:38.825
My son.

43:38.991 --> 43:41.702
I trust they will allow him
letters at this wretched school.

43:45.456 --> 43:48.709
Last night... at the table...

43:48.876 --> 43:50.461
I think it would be good
for all of us

43:50.628 --> 43:52.380
if we were to return to London.

43:54.549 --> 43:57.468
Relations between the inmates
of a country house party

43:57.635 --> 43:59.846
can very soon become...

44:00.012 --> 44:01.514
eccentric.

44:07.061 --> 44:09.981
Where is, um...
I don't know his name.

44:10.148 --> 44:11.440
The large fellow?

44:11.607 --> 44:13.734
Joseph, Your Grace.

44:13.901 --> 44:15.444
He has been dismissed.

44:15.611 --> 44:17.947
Whatever for?

44:18.114 --> 44:20.867
Skipping church, ma'am.

44:21.033 --> 44:23.411
II'

44:29.876 --> 44:30.877
K! Good.

44:31.043 --> 44:36.424
II'

44:38.926 --> 44:40.386
S! Good.

